{[%evp 0,45,21,17,26,26,26,18,18,2,2,2,37,46,78,20,31,-1,-18,8,-2,-22,-1,-2,82,67,48,46,49,49,31,27,20,22,32,41,46,56,63,63,54,53,53,46,77,21,21,46]} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. d4 exd4 5. Nxd4 {Here} Bc5 $5 {is still popular, although it is inferior to the main move 5...Bb4.} 6. Be3 $1 {Undoubtedly the best reply.} (6. Nxc6 $5 {is also a decent try, regarding that the bishop is placed better on b4 than on the current c5-square.} bxc6 7. Bd3 O-O 8. O-O Re8 9. h3 Bd4 10. Re1 $14) 6... Bb6 7. Qd2 (7. Nf5 $5 {is a lazy way to fight for a slight advantage -} O-O 8. Bxb6 axb6 9. Ne3 Re8 10. Bd3 d6 (10... b5 $5 {is promising some counterplay}) 11. O-O Nd7 (11... Ne5 12. a4 $14) 12. f4 Nc5 13. Qh5 $16 {Carlsen - Aronian, San Fermin Masters Final chess24. com INT 2021.}) 7... O-O 8. O-O-O Re8 (8... Ng4 {was effectively met by} 9. Bg5 $1 f6 10. Nxc6 bxc6 11. Bh4 Qe8 12. h3 Ne5 (12... Nh6 13. f4 $16) 13. f4 Nf7 14. Bd3 $16 {C. Debray - M. Turov, Lille, 2012.}) 9. f3 d5 $1 {The only real chance to fight for the equality. Otherwise, Black has a cramped and passive version of the Scotch, as demonstrated by the following practical examples:} (9... d6 10. g4 Nxd4 11. Bxd4 Be6 12. Kb1 Nd7 13. Be2 Qh4 14. f4 $16 {M. Bagi - J. Pechac, Pardubice, Czech op-A, 2015}) (9... Ne5 10. Nb3 $5 d6 11. Be2 Be6 12. g4 Nc4 13. Bxc4 Bxc4 14. g5 Nd7 {Soffer - Smirin, ISR-chT, 2019,} 15. h4 $1 $16) 10. exd5 Nxd5 11. Bg5 $1 {The same bishop sally is annoying as ever.} f6 (11... Nde7 {is probably safer, but after} 12. Nxc6 Qxd2+ 13. Bxd2 Nxc6 14. Nd5 Ne7 15. Nxb6 axb6 16. a3 $14 {there is no compensation for the bishop's pair in an open position.}) 12. Bc4 Nxd4 $8 13. Nxd5 Be6 $8 14. Bxf6 $1 {The exact move order.} (14. Nxb6 $143 axb6 15. Qxd4 Qxd4 16. Bxe6+ Rxe6 17. Rxd4 fxg5 18. a3 Re2 $132) 14... gxf6 15. Nxb6 axb6 16. Qxd4 $8 Qxd4 17. Bxe6+ Rxe6 18. Rxd4 Rxa2 19. Kb1 Ra5 20. Rd7 Rc5 ({Very similar is} 20... Re2 21. Rhd1 Rc5 22. R1d2 $14 {L. Medarde Santiago - F. Sanchez Aller, 1st Santiago de Compostela 2018.}) 21. Rhd1 h5 22. c3 Re2 23. R1d2 $14 {Despite the material balance, Black is about to suffer a lot because of his spoiled pawn structure, Szulc - Wiesinger, ICCF email, 2019.} *

